</node>
<node id="xixi">
  <data key="d0">xixi</data>
  <data key="d1">product</data>
  <data key="d2">Xixi is a colloquial term for urine, which was used in early methods to test for sugar levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="1964">
  <data key="d0">1964</data>
  <data key="d1">year</data>
  <data key="d2">The year 1964 saw the introduction of the first blood glucose meter that measured sugar levels from a single drop of blood.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AMGC">
  <data key="d0">AMGC</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">AMGC (Automonitoramento da Glicemia Capilar) is a method of monitoring blood glucose levels using small punctures on the finger and a glucometer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monitoramento contínuo de glicose (SMCG)">
  <data key="d0">Monitoramento contínuo de glicose (SMCG)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">SMCG (Sensor Monitor Contínuo de Glicose) is a method of continuously monitoring blood glucose levels using sensors attached to the skin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sensor flash de glicose">
  <data key="d0">Sensor flash de glicose</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Sensor "flash" de glicose is a type of sensor that measures blood glucose levels and requires a reader to display the results.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Medidores que funcionam como um relógio ou uma lente de contato">
  <data key="d0">Medidores que funcionam como um relógio ou uma lente de contato</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">These are new types of sensors being developed that function like a watch or contact lens to measure blood glucose levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1589a8affdd5757e262b758cb4998689</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1767907606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Medidores que usam luz ou calor, sem precisar furar o dedo">
  <data key="d0">Medidores que usam luz ou calor, sem precisar furar o dedo</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">These are new types of sensors being developed that use light or heat without needing to puncture the skin.</data>
